    "text": "Start with duration consistency, because that's where your data shows the most room. Last night you slept 7 hours while your 7-day average is 7.4, so recent nights are wobbling around rather than holding steady, and steadiness is what your recovery responds to; today's 63% is decent but not where your 65% weekly average could climb with more regular nights. Your heart signals look healthy, HRV at 52 ms is slightly above its 50.1 ms 30-day average, so this is fine-tuning, not repair. The single highest-leverage change: fix your wake time, even on weekends, and let bedtime drift earlier naturally. Add a wind-down cue in the last half hour, dim lights, no work. One limitation worth knowing: your tracker isn't reporting sleep stages here, so duration and morning recovery are the honest scoreboard. Revisit in two weeks and see if the weekly average moved.",
